hes and it also endeavors – with the help of the historic/political parallel of the bourgeois revolutions in the 19th century – to define the corporate polity. The second part analyses the new kind of political operational logic from the viewpoint of the different areas of corporate operation; it gives an overview of the consequences for the individual areas of operation and indicates how corporate policy can be realized in the given field of operation. The third part of the book introduces the institutions necessary for the creation of the corporate polity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aCorporate governancexMoral and ethical aspects. 0aSocial responsibility of business. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Corporate Governance.2bisacsh  aBusiness, Capitalism, Corporate Social Responsibility, Marketing, Sustainability.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2019z978311078051240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633862940423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633862940/original  a978-3-11-078051-2  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK